This paper deals with energy-efficient protocols for LTE femtocell networks, which are primarily related to networking and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses interference mitigation, which is a key component of the proposed protocol and involves signal processing and information theory (cs.IT). The use of distributed algorithms for UE association and OFDMA scheduling suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The simulations conducted in the paper involve measuring multiple metrics such as power consumption and convergence speed, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC), respectively.
